# Docker after changes

Whenever you modify files in this repository as part of the work (code, static assets, Docker config, env examples, etc.), **clean-restart the stack** from the project root so the running container matches the tree. Do this **after** your edits for that turn are done, not only when the user asks.

Run this exact sequence (full recycle, not `up` alone):

```bash
cd /home/jaybird/jayprograms/dashbird && docker compose down && docker compose up -d --build && docker compose logs lan-url
```

- `down` stops and removes containers so stale state does not linger.
- `up -d --build` rebuilds images when needed and starts detached.
- `lan-url` logs print the same-Wi-Fi phone URL for bookmarking.

If `down` fails because nothing was running, continue with `up -d --build` and `logs lan-url`.

Skip the restart only when the change cannot affect the running stack (e.g. docs-only with no runtime impact) — when in doubt, run the clean restart.
